t/execution and lifecycle hook invocation for one plugin. Hypothetical elsewhere: Node version-specific module loader quirks, filesystem watcher timing. MOCK-MISS: testing onLoad caller alone misses import-execution ordering bug. REAL-INFRA: can be validated in-process with local test modules; no subprocess/network required by behavior text. MOCK-HIDE: if import is fully mocked, you may miss missing-await/ordering defects; use real module import within test process. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: none. Rejection gate: System considered but rejected because behavior text does not require cross-process or external OS behavior, only loader sequencing around import and hook.","test_description":"Create a plugin entry module that sets `globalThis.entryExecuted = true` at top-level and exports onLoad that snapshots that flag. Run loader. Assert onLoad was called and observed `entryExecuted === true` at invocation time.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its onLoad hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Observed in this behavior: error isolation plus dependency-aware continuation across multiple plugins. Hypothetical elsewhere: crash recovery after process restart, remote plugin fetch failures. MOCK-MISS: requires real interaction among dependency graph, hook runner, and error handling policy; unit scope is too narrow. REAL-INFRA: no external OS/network/subprocess dependency required by behavior text. MOCK-HIDE: stubbing graph or runner can hide incorrect skip/continue behavior. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: none. Rejection gate: System rejected because behavior is about in-process control flow after onLoad exception, not real infrastructure behavior.","test_description":"Set up plugins: X throws in onLoad; Y has no